{{Infobox company | name = Flutura Decision Sciences and Analytics | logo =Flutura-Logo.png | logo_size =150px | type =[[Private company|Private Ltd.]] | location_city ={{Unbulleted list|[[Bangalore]], [[Karnataka]], India| [[Palo Alto, California]]}} | founder ={{Unbulleted list|Krishnan Raman|Derick Jose|Srikanth Muralidhara}} | foundation =February 2012 | industry =[[Machine to Machine]], [[Internet of Things]], [[Big Data]] [[Analytics]], [[Decision science]]s | products = {{Unbulleted list|Cerebra}} | homepage ={{URL|flutura.com}} }}
'''Flutura Decision Sciences and Analytics''' is an Industrial [[Internet of things]] (IoT) company that focuses on [[machine to machine]] and [[big data]] analytics serving clients from manufacturing, energy and engineering industries. Its main offices are located in [[Palo Alto, California]] and has its development centre in Bengaluru, India.
== History == Flutura was co-founded by Krishnan Raman, Srikanth Muralidhara, and Derick Jose, in February 2012. Raman, formerly from [[Mindtree]], became the chief executive.<ref>{{Cite web |title= Krishnan Raman: CEO, Flutura |work= E-Commerce Summit promotional site |publisher= VC Circle |url= http://events.vccircle.com/content/krishnan-raman |access-date= May 21, 2017 }}</ref> The word 'Flutura' means butterfly in Albanian. Flutura developed software called Cerebra, announced by 2013.<ref>{{Cite web |title= Flutura Solutions: Help 'See' Previously 'Unseen' Patterns |date= October 3, 2013 |work= CIO Review |author= Benita Matilda |url= http://www.cioreview.com/crtech-india/10-most-promising-big-data-companies.html |deadurl= yes |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20131016054947/http://www.cioreview.com/crtech-india/10-most-promising-big-data-companies.html |archivedate= October 16, 2013 |access-date= May 21, 2017 |df= }}</ref>
A [[Henkel]] factory in China was using Cerebra in 2016.<ref>{{Cite web |title= This Indian IoT Product In China Shows How Factories Will Be Part Of The 4th Revolution |author= Sumit Chakraberty |date= October 12, 2016 |work= Forbes |url= https://www.forbes.com/sites/sumitchakraberty/2016/10/12/why-henkel-dragon-plant-in-china-is-using-indian-iot-product-flutura/ |access-date= May 21, 2017 }}</ref> The same year, [[Hitachi]] announced it would sell the software in Japan.<ref>{{Cite news |title= Hitachi High-Tech Solutions partners with Flutura to bring Industrial IOT intelligence to Japanese businesses |date= September 15, 2016 |work= Press release |publisher= Hitachi |url= http://www.hitachi-hightech.com/global/about/news/2016/nr20160915.html |access-date= May 21, 2017 }}</ref> The company announced US$7.5 million of [[venture capital]] in February 2017, led by the sovereign wealth fund of Singapore [[Temasek Holdings]].<ref>{{Cite news |title= Behind India’s largest series A round in IoT: how Flutura chose its investors |author= Sumit Chakraberty |work= Tech in Asia |date= February 12, 2017 |url= https://www.techinasia.com/flutura-gets-funding-to-crack-industrial-iot |access-date= May 21, 2017 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title= IoT data analytics firm Flutura raises $7.5M led by Vertex Ventures |author= Shadma Shaikh |work= Economic Times India |date= February 13, 2017 |url= http://tech.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/startups/iot-data-analytics-firm-flutura-business-solutions-raises-7-5m-led-by-vertex-ventures/57119280 |access-date= May 21, 2017 }}</ref>
